<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<jmeterTestPlan version="1.2" properties="5.0" jmeter="5.6.3">
  <hashTree>
    <TestPlan guiclass="TestPlanGui" testclass="TestPlan" testname="Flash Sale — Checkout Stress Test">
      <stringProp name="TestPlan.comments">
Concurrent checkout stress test — proves the concurrency story.

HOW TO RUN (locked version — current build):
  jmeter -n -t checkout-stress-test.jmx -l results-locked.jtl -e -o report-locked/

HOW TO RUN (unlocked version — for comparison):
  1. In OrderService.checkout(), comment out the Redisson lock block:
       RLock lock = redissonClient.getLock(...);
       lock.tryLock(...);
       cacheService.deleteCache(...);   ← keep this
       ... deductStock ...              ← keep this
       lock.unlock();
       cacheService.scheduleSecondDeletion(...);  ← keep this
     Specifically: remove tryLock/unlock calls; keep cacheService + deductStock.
  2. Rebuild the app.
  3. jmeter -n -t checkout-stress-test.jmx -l results-unlocked.jtl -e -o report-unlocked/

WHAT TO LOOK FOR:
  Locked   — exactly INITIAL_STOCK checkouts succeed (200); rest get 409. finalStock = 0.
  Unlocked — may get MORE than INITIAL_STOCK successes (oversell). finalStock &lt; 0 in logs.

BEFORE RUNNING:
  1. Update PRODUCT_ID to a valid active product (check Postman or MySQL)
  2. Update ADMIN_USERNAME / ADMIN_PASSWORD
  3. Ensure the Spring Boot app is running on localhost:8080
      </stringProp>
      <boolProp name="TestPlan.serialize_threadgroups">true</boolProp>
